ype, and snapshot pages via structured commands.\r\n  Body: 1. Navigate: `agent-browser open <url>` 2. Snapshot: `agent-browser snapshot -i` (returns elements with refs like `@e1`, `@e2`) 3. Interact using refs from the snapshot 4. Re-snapshot after navigation or significant DOM \r\n  Path: D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\skill-library\\agent-browser\r\nagent-cli\r\n  Summary: Comprehensive local agent-CLI playbook for choosing and using OpenCode (`opencode`), Harness (`harness`), and Codex CLI (`codex`). Use when Codex needs to route a task to the right local coding-agent CLI, run CLI agents from PowerShell, compare capabilities, use browser/multi-model workflows, manage sessions, review code, attach skill/rule files, create OpenCode native agents, inspect model/provider state, configure safety modes, or explain reliable agent-CLI command patterns.\r\n  Body: Use this skill as the unified operating guide for the three local coding-agent CLIs available on this machine:\r\n  Path: D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\skill-library\\agent-cli\r\nagent-workflow\r\n  Summary: Agent workflow framework for building and operating long-lived, step-based workflows on top of `mycli agent-cli`. Use when the task involves `workflow.json`, step scaffolding, listener/webhook waiting, review gates, run status inspection, event injection, or controlled multi-step agent orchestration under D:\\\\agent_workspace\\\\capability-library\\\\agent-system-rules\\\\agent-workflow.\r\n  Body: Use this capability when the task should be modeled as a workflow rather than a single agent invocation.\r\n  Path: D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\skill-library\\agent-workflow\r\naliyun-server-operation\r\n  Summary: 阿里云 ECS 服务器远程操作指南。Use when connecting to, inspecting, or operating the Aliyun server at 39.106.125.149 from this workspace, especially via PuTTY plink password-based SSH, PowerShell-cli, PM2, systemd, 宝塔面板, and Chat Soft server files.\r\n  Body: 本 skill 记录当前工作区可直接操作的