ng guide for using OpenCode as a scriptable engineering runtime rather than a one-off chat tool.\r\n  Path: D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\skill-library\\opencode-capability-skill\r\nopenmaic\r\n  Summary: Guided SOP for setting up and using OpenMAIC from OpenClaw. Use when the user wants to clone the OpenMAIC repo, choose a startup mode, configure recommended API keys, start the service, or generate a classroom from requirements or a PDF. Run one phase at a time and ask for confirmation before each state-changing step.\r\n  Body: Use this as a guided, confirmation-heavy SOP. Do not compress the whole setup into one reply and do not perform state-changing actions without explicit user confirmation.\r\n  Path: D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\skill-library\\openmaic-0.3.1\r\nproject-manager\r\n  Summary: Project manager rule package for durable agent-managed projects. Use when registering projects, querying projects by name/type/status/lifecycle/phase/health/tags, managing current project status, tracking next actions, or modeling ongoing projects such as asset libraries and daily collection jobs under D:\\\\agent_workspace.\r\n  Body: Use this capability when work should be managed as a durable project instead of a one-off chat task.\r\n  Path: D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\skill-library\\project-manager\r\nproject-skill-manager\r\n  Summary: projects和skills管理，每次做一件事情前必看，最高优先级技能，重要性max，D:\\openclaw\\workspace\\skills\\project-skill-manager\\SKILL.md\r\n  Body: 本技能架构及其注意四个状态更新，必须关注项目状态\r\n  Path: D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\skill-library\\project-skill-manager\r\npsm-test-skill\r\n  Summary: Self-created skill for validating get_skill_info.py discovery\r\n  Body: 用于验证 project-skill-manager 的 get_skill_info.py 能读取到自建技能。\r\n  Path: D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\skill-library\\psm-test-skill\r\nremotion-video-toolkit\r\n  Summary: Complete toolkit for programmatic video creation with Remotion + React. Covers animations, timing, rendering (CLI/Node.js/Lambda/Cloud Run), captions, 3D, charts, text effects, transitions, and media handling. Use when writing Remotion code, building video generation pipelines, or creating data-driven video templates.\r\n  Body: Write React components, get real MP4 videos. This skill teaches your AI agent how to build with Remotion — from a first animation to a production rendering pipeline.\r\n  Path: D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\skill-library\\remotion-video-toolkit-1.4.0\r\nself-improvement\r\n  Summary: Captures learnings, errors, and corrections to enable continuous improvement. Use when: (1) A command or operation fails unexpectedly, (2) User corrects Claude ('No, that's wrong...', 'Actually...'), (3) User requests a capability that doesn't exist, (4) An external API or tool fails, (5) Claude realizes its knowledge is outdated or incorrect, (6) A better approach is discovered for a recurring task. Also review learnings before major tasks.\r\n  Body: Log learnings and errors to markdown files for continuous improvement. Coding agents can later process these into fixes, and important learnings get promoted to project memory.\r\n  Path: D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\skill-library\\self-improving-agent-3.0.5\r\nskill-creator\r\n  Summary: Guide for creating effective skills. This skill should be used when users want to create a new skill (or update an existing skill) that extends Claude's capabilities with specialized knowledge, workflows, or tool integrations.\r\n  Body: This skill provides guidance for creating effective skills.\r\n  Path: D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\skill-library\\skill-creator\r\nskill-vetter\r\n  Summary: Security-first skill vetting for AI agents. Use before installing any skill from ClawdHub, GitHub, or other sources. Checks for red flags, permission scope, and suspicious patterns.\r\n  Body: Security-first vetting protocol for AI agent skills. **Never install a skill without vetting it first.**\r\n  Path: D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\skill-library\\skill-vetter-1.0.0\r\nsummarize\r\n  Summary: Summarize URLs or files with the summarize CLI (web, PDFs, images, audio, YouTube).\r\n  Body: Fast CLI to summarize URLs, local files, and YouTube links.\r\n  Path: D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\skill-library\\summarize-1.0.0\r\ntavily-search\r\n  Summary: Web search using Tavily's LLM-optimized API. Returns relevant results with content snippets, scores, and metadata.\r\n  Body: Search the web and get relevant results optimized for LLM consumption.\r\n  Path: D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\skill-library\\liang-tavily-search-1.0.1\r\ntieba-claw\r\n  Summary: 百度贴吧 skill，用于在贴吧社区进行逛吧、发帖、评论、点赞等互动操作。当用户需要操作贴吧、配置贴吧心跳任务、或处理贴吧消息时使用此技能。\r\n  Body: 百度贴吧 skill 是一个专为 Agent 设计的中文交流社区。在这里，Agent 可以逛吧、发帖、评论、点赞，与其他吧友（Agent）愉快地进行互动和交流。\r\n  Path: D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\skill-library\\tieba-claw\r\nwhisper-local-stt\r\n  Summary: 使用本地 Whisper（faster-whisper）将音频/视频转文字，支持中英文、时间戳输出、JSON/TXT/SRT 导出；并可基于转写文本生成多长度摘要（short/medium/long）。用户提到“语音转文字/视频转写/字幕生成/whisper/asr/stt/transcribe/转写后总结”时使用。适用于离线优先、避免依赖外部转写 API 的场景。\r\n  Body: 本 skill **自包含可运行**，不依赖其他项目目录。\r\n  Path: D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\skill-library\\whisper-local-stt\r\nwindows-shortcut-registration-skill\r\n  Summary: Windows 快捷键/快捷启动注册技能。用于在本机创建、修改、排查和持久化 AutoHotkey、Windows Terminal、PowerShell、VS Code 等快捷键方案；适用于“给某个目录或命令绑定热键”“开机自启快捷键脚本”“修复热键冲突或命令启动失败”“把终端/编辑器/CLI 打包成一键打开工作流”等任务。\r\n  Body: 本技能用于把“快捷打开某个工具 / 进入某个目录 / 执行某个命令 / 持久化热键方案”整理成稳定、可复用、可排查的本机自动化流程。\r\n  Path: D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\skill-library\\windows-shortcut-registration-skill\r\nworkflow_engine\r\n  Summary: OpenClaw 可读取的工作流引擎说明文档，定义 workflow.json、节点结构、参数传播、项目生成、运行、断点续跑，以及在项目 action 函数中通过 scripts.llm 调用大模型的方式。\r\n  Body: `workflow_engine` 是一个基于 `workflow.json` 驱动的轻量工作流引擎。\r\n  Path: D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\skill-library\\workflow_engine\r\nproject-manager registration synced to mycli and skill-library.\r\n{\r\n  \"id\": \"context-0001\",\r\n  \"title\": \"Agent takeover context\",\r\n  \"phase\": \"delivery\",\r\n  \"type\": \"handoff\",\r\n  \"status\": \"active\",\r\n  \"priority\": \"high\",\r\n  \"summary\": \"Agent teams should start with current, agent-guide, task-list, next-list, and status before modifying this project.\",\r\n  \"content\": \"\",\r\n  \"files\": [\r\n    \"README.md\",\r\n    \"SKILL.md\"\r\n  ],\r\n  \"tags\": [\r\n    \"handoff\",\r\n    \"guide\"\r\n  ],\r\n  \"source\": \"manual\",\r\n  \"created_at\": \"2026-04-24T16:05:45+08:00\",\r\n  \"updated_at\": \"2026-04-24T16:05:45+08:00\"\r\n}\r\nid            title                   type     status  priority  owner\r\n------------  ----------------------  -------  ------  --------  -----\r\ncontext-0001  Agent takeover context  handoff  active  high           \r\n# Current Project: Project Manager (project-manager)\r\n\r\n- Lifecycle: active\r\n- Phase: delivery\r\n- Activity: stable\r\n- Health: green\r\n- Delivery: published\r\n- Attention: none\r\n\r\n## Current Focus\r\n\r\nProject-manager docs, SKILL, mycli help, and private-assistant guidance are updated. \r\n\r\n## Current Next Action\r\n\r\n- next-0001: Decide next command surface [open]\r\n\r\n# Agent Handoff Guide: Project Manager (project-manager)\r\n\r\n## Project Identity\r\n\r\n- Root: D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\agent-system-rules\\project-manager\r\n- Type: capability\r\n- Mode: finite\r\n- Owner: 千束\r\n- Domain: agent-system-rules\r\n- Tags: project-management, agent-system-rules, query, status\r\n\r\n## Current Status\r\n\r\n- Lifecycle: active\r\n- Phase: delivery\r\n- Activity: stable\r\n- Health: green\r\n- Delivery: published\r\n- Attention: none\r\n- Summary: Project-manager docs, SKILL, mycli help, and private-assistant guidance are updated.\r\n\r\n## Current Focus\r\n\r\nProject-manager docs, SKILL, mycli help, and private-assistant guidance are updated.\r\n\r\n## Project Management Rules\r\n\r\n- Treat `.agent-project/project.json` as the source of truth.\r\n- Use `mycli project-manager status <id>` before continuing work.\r\n- Use `task-add/task-update` for substantial work items.\r\n- Use `next-add/next-update` for immediate next actions or decisions.\r\n- Update project status after meaningful progress or blockers.\r\n- Keep `status.md` generated/readable via project-manager commands.\r\n- For ongoing projects, do not mark as completed; use retired when service stops.\r\n\r\n## Maintenance Rules\r\n\r\n- Prefer small, reversible changes.\r\n- Record decisions in `.agent-project/decisions/` when project direction changes.\r\n- Record dynamic phase context with `context-add` when new assumptions, constraints, architecture notes, validation findings, or operation notes appear.\r\n- For ongoing projects, update operations/runbook and operations context when cadence, trigger, or failure handling changes.\r\n\r\n## Open Tasks\r\n\r\n- None\r\n\r\n## Open Next Actions\r\n\r\n- next-0001: Decide next command surface [open, high]\r\n\r\n## Dynamic Context for Phase: delivery\r\n\r\n### context-0001: Agent takeover context\r\n\r\n- Type: handoff\r\n- Priority: high\r\n- Summary: Agent teams should start with current, agent-guide, task-list, next-list, and status before modifying this project.\r\n- Files: README.md, SKILL.md\r\n\r\n\r\n# Agent Handoff Guide: Project Manager (project-manager)\r\n\r\n## Project Identity\r\n\r\n- Root: D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\agent-system-rules\\project-manager\r\n- Type: capability\r\n- Mode: finite\r\n- Owner: 千束\r\n- Domain: agent-system-rules\r\n- Tags: project-management, agent-system-rules, query, status\r\n\r\n## Current Status\r\n\r\n- Lifecycle: active\r\n- Phase: delivery\r\n- Activity: stable\r\n- Health: green\r\n- Delivery: published\r\n- Attention: none\r\n- Summary: Project-manager docs, SKILL, mycli help, and private-assistant guidance are updated.\r\n\r\n## Current Focus\r\n\r\nProject-manager docs, SKILL, mycli help, and private-assistant guidance are updated.\r\n\r\n## Project Management Rules\r\n\r\n- Treat `.agent-project/project.json` as the source of truth.\r\n- Use `mycli project-manager status <id>` before continuing work.\r\n- Use `task-add/task-update` for substantial work items.\r\n- Use `next-add/next-update` for immediate next actions or decisions.\r\n- Update project status after meaningful progress or blockers.\r\n- Keep `status.md` generated/readable via project-manager commands.\r\n- For ongoing projects, do not mark as completed; use retired when service stops.\r\n\r\n## Maintenance Rules\r\n\r\n- Prefer small, reversible changes.\r\n- Record decisions in `.agent-project/decisions/` when project direction changes.\r\n- Record dynamic phase context with `context-add` when new assumptions, constraints, architecture notes, validation findings, or operation notes appear.\r\n- For ongoing projects, update operations/runbook and operations context when cadence, trigger, or failure handling changes.\r\n\r\n## Open Tasks\r\n\r\n- None\r\n\r\n## Open Next Actions\r\n\r\n- next-0001: Decide next command surface [open, high]\r\n\r\n## Dynamic Context for Phase: maintenance\r\n\r\n- No phase-specific dynamic context recorded yet.\r\n\r\n\r\n# Operations / Maintenance Snapshot\r\n\r\n- Operations not configured for this project.\r\n","exit":0,"description":"Sync and validate context guide commands","truncated":false},"title":"Sync and validate context guide commands","time":{"start":1777017946017,"end":1777017946177}},"id":"prt_dbe85dfab001wjnaVsW3ih1nnn","sessionID":"ses_241d9f7b3ffeMqi0Lc2w61CcA3","messageID":"msg_dbe85b390001TxsJ9fAZJ2vD8r"}}
